# Galáticos Core

Sports roster management: JSON API (Ring/Compojure) + Reagent SPA (shadow-cljs).

## Stack (verify in deps.edn before adding libs)

| Layer | Libraries |
|-------|-----------|
| JVM | Clojure 1.11, Ring, Compojure, Jetty, Buddy JWT, Environ, Selmer/Hiccup |
| DB | MongoDB via **Monger 3.x** — not raw Java driver APIs in handlers |
| CLJS | shadow-cljs, Reagent, reitit-frontend, cljs-http, Tailwind |
| Build | `deps.edn` aliases `:test`, `:cljs-test`, `:uberjar`, `:coverage`, `:format` |

## Code layout

- `src/galaticos/handlers/` — request logic
- `src/galaticos/routes/` — Compojure routes (aggregator: `routes/api.clj`)
- `src/galaticos/db/` — Mongo access
- `src/galaticos/middleware/` — auth, CORS, errors, gzip
- `src-cljs/galaticos/components/` — UI
- `src-cljs/galaticos/routes.cljs` — client routing

Namespaces: `src/galaticos/...` and `src-cljs/galaticos/...` — not `src/main/clj/`.

## Do not use unless declared in deps.edn

Rails, ActiveRecord, Stimulus/Hotwire, Luminus mount/component/integrant patterns.

## Change discipline

- Minimal, focused diffs; match existing style (kebab-case, small functions)
- Conventional commits: `feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `refactor:`
- Do not edit compiled assets under `resources/public/js/compiled/`

## Verify after changes

```bash
./bin/galaticos test
./bin/galaticos coverage   # when touching backend logic
```

Run clj-kondo when editing `.clj` / `.cljs`. Docs: `docs/README.md`.
